The full suite passed: 87 tests run, 41 optional-`pytz` tests skipped. The code trace confirms ordinary boundary handling, but it also exposes two untested clause interactions: lowering a budget after prior runs is only noticed after another call, and a raising job never reaches the post-call counter increment. I’m executing both scenarios now, alongside the required multi-job/`run_all()` interaction, to distinguish concrete failures from reading-only concerns.
